attributes.value: Smutsia temminckii
Hollow trees and burrows in savanna and woodland areas across the southern and eastern regions of the African continent.
Pangolins are the only mammal which is wholly covered in scales. When in immediate danger they curl into a ball and thrash out at an attacker with their sharp-edged tail.
Pangolins are the most trafficked animal in the world. All 8 species range from highly vulnerable to critically endangered.
Bombus pensylvanicus
14-25 mm, all between 150-200 mg
A range of open habitats, including farmlands, meadows, and grasslands across Eastern Canada, Central and Eastern regions of the US and much of Mexico.
In defense from predation, American bumblebees uses Müllarian and Batesian mimicry, two methods of anti-detection often found in the insect world.
As of January 2023, the American bumblebee population had declined by 90% since the year 2000.

Panthera uncia
2.1 m long, 80-105 cm tail, 23-41 kg
Steep, jagged landscapes, such as cliffs, rocky outcrops, and ravines, at altitudes of 3,000-4,500 m.
The paws of a snow leopard act as snowshoes, allowing them to move across deep snow without sinking though.

Possibly as few as 4,000 individuals remain in the wild. They are extremely elusive creatures and live in such harsh environments that their struggle for survival in a warming world goes mostly unnoticed.

Danaus plexippus
About 10 cm wingspan, 0.5 grams
Prairies, meadows, and grasslands across North America.
In the winter the Monarch Butterfly migrates from the north of the continent to the south, traveling distances from 2,000 up to 4,500 km.

A decline of nearly one billion monarch butterflies between 1990 and 2015 has been recorded. This is especially noticeable in the United States, with some areas in the west experiencing an estimated decline of 99.9%.

Diceros bicornis
African scrublands, tropical and subtropical grasslands, montanes forests, and savannas.
Black rhinos have a hooked prehensile upper lip, allowing them to eat from branches and bushes, unlike white rhinos, who graze at ground level and have a square shaped upper lip.
Black Rhinoceros are critically endangered because of high demand for their horns. Between 2008 and 2021, around 11,000 of the animals were killed by poachers.

Ornithorhynchus anatinus
Australian and Tasmanian freshwater creeks, slow-moving rivers, lakes joined by rivers, and built water storages such as farm dams.
A preserved specimen of the semiaquatic, egg-legging mammal was first deemed a fake by skeptical 16th century European naturalists.
The duck-billed platypus is threatened by human modifications to its habitat. The current population could be nearly half of previous estimates.
